  "prompt": "What is months at level in Accenture?",
  "response": "In Accenture, \"Months at Level\" refers to the length of time an employee has spent at their current job level or position. This metric is often used to assess career progression, performance, and readiness for promotion or role changes. It helps Accenture and its employees track how long someone has been in a specific role and whether they are due for advancement or need additional development opportunities.\n\nUnderstanding and managing \"Months at Level\" is important for career planning, as it aligns with Accenture's performance management and promotion cycles. Employees and their managers typically discuss this during performance reviews to ensure career growth aligns with organizational goals. \n\nIf you\u2019re an Accenture employee, you can find your \"Months at Level\" in your performance dashboard or through discussions with your People Lead or HR representative.",
